title.narrative: By 2025, UNICEF Staff and partners have mechanisms in place to deliver quality social and behavioural change interventions

description.narrative: Reached eight million people through interpersonal communication and another 10 million people through mass communication, maintaining a high level of awareness on prevention and vaccination against COVID19. The Government led Social and Behavioral Change Communication (SBCC) intervention has been more systematic, ensuring better budget allocation and intervention than in previous years. AAP strategy and multi-years workplan have been developed and endorsed in collaboration with the emergency unit to integrate the concept across thematic areas. Community feedback is being collected and compiled using various platforms. Four mobile device-based applications are being used to automate SBCC related monitoring, evaluation and supportive supervision. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2021
